cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DB (Database): The paper focuses on how persistence is supported through external SQL database management systems, which is a core topic in database research. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses how the deductive expressive power is projected to relational databases, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper describes how persistent predicates have been included in the deductive system DES, which is a logical system. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper explains the implementation and some optimizations of intermixing computations of the deductive engine and the external database, which is a software engineering problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper introduces how persistence is supported from a user-point of view, which is related to programming language design.
